KMFDMAdios008D.name: KMFDM BRUTE Adios d #008
description: This is my favourite KMFDM artwork because it was the first
project on which I'd used the multiple perspective
technique. Rather than have the shapes and dynamics flood
outwards from a solitary vanishing point, I began instead to
design a 'firework display' of impact zones that each
held their own dramatic core whilst adhering to an instinctive
horizon. Its not a technique that is easily adaptable to less
dramatic subjects but Crash/Adios certainly illustrates what I
was trying to do at the time. The floating in-car debris is a
nod to the work of Geof Darrow whose Hard Boiled comics were a
big inspiration in the early 90s. - BRUTE!
